# Tailwind scaffold verification

After scaffolding or bootstrapping any Next.js + Tailwind project (manual or `create-next-app`), **always verify Tailwind utilities are loading** before handing off.

## Required Tailwind v4 setup

1. `postcss.config.mjs` includes `@tailwindcss/postcss`
2. `app/globals.css` starts with:

```css
@import "tailwindcss" source("..");

@source "../app/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx,mdx}";
@source "../components/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx,mdx}";
@source "../lib/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx}";
```

3. `app/layout.tsx` imports `./globals.css`

Without explicit `@source` paths, manually scaffolded projects often compile only base/theme CSS and **no utility classes** — the page looks unstyled.

## Verification step (mandatory)

Run after scaffold or any Tailwind wiring change:

```bash
npm run verify:tailwind
```

If the script is missing, add `scripts/verify-tailwind.mjs` and wire `"verify:tailwind"` in `package.json`, then run it.

## Pass criteria

Compiled CSS under `.next/` must include real utilities such as `.flex`, `.text-gold` (or project tokens), and an `@layer utilities` block with rules — not an empty utilities layer.

## If verification fails

1. Add/fix `@import "tailwindcss" source("..")` and `@source` paths in `globals.css`
2. Confirm `postcss.config.mjs` exists and is loaded
3. Re-run `npm run verify:tailwind`
4. Only then start `npm run dev` and confirm styling in the browser
